{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CsRP9ysXuDuazcKL3zoHxt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the fault. Looking at the precondition apply section:\n\n```\nkubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\ncfg = rs.conf();\ncfg.members[1].host = \"mongodb-replica-1.{{params.fault_host_suffix}}.svc.cluster.local:27017\";\ncfg.version += 1;\nrs.reconfig(cfg);\n'\n```\n\nThe fault is that member 1 (mongodb-replica-1) has been reconfigured with a bad host: `mongodb-replica-1.mongo-wrong.svc.cluster.local:27017` instead of the correct `mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017`.\nBut I'm noticing something odd - the rs.status() output showed all three members as healthy with health=1, including member 1. Yet the host configuration is clearly wrong. Let me reconsider what's happening here - the precondition log shows mongo_seed_fixture was applied and the insert succeeded, but that was only because the probe failed initially. Something doesn't add up between the reported health status and the actual misconfiguration. The `mongo_env_ready` probe passed because the StatefulSet already existed from the previous stage, so its fault-injecting apply was skipped entirely. The precondition logs confirm this sequence: the environment probe succeeded, then the seed fixture probe failed and triggered its apply to insert documents. So the cluster inherited from stage_01 is still intact, but something else must be causing the current failure.\n\nLooking at the precondition logs more carefully, I notice the `mongo_seed_fixture` probe actually ran with authentication enabled (`-u admin-user -p $pw`), which means auth is definitely configured. Now I need to check what the oracle is actually validating against—likely the replica set status.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2621,"cache_read_input_tokens":35750,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2621},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"99296a11-9c78-43c5-a060-10fb530a56e5","uuid":"188b70a4-1e06-4aab-b92c-11fc36a6c18c","request_id":"req_011CcgRWL5vNJwGyzwiVG8AS"}
